post_text:
Reopening Survey Information

At the August 10, 2020 Board Meeting, the Clifton Board of Education presented the Clifton Public Schools Restart and Reopening Plan to be submitted to the New Jersey Department of Education. You will receive an email to select which "return to school option" you prefer for your child. For the district to prepare the best possible environment for students and staff for September, we rely on your responses. You can review the plan and presentations on the district website by visiting this link: https://www.clifton.k12.nj.us/Page/4776.

A separate survey must be completed for each child in your household. You may receive multiple emails.

You may also respond to the survey with your child's ID number by clicking on the following link:
https://clifton.sjc1.qualtrics.com/jfe/form/SV_6L3ZaHT0ydfanxr

Please submit your responses by Monday, August 17, 2020.

Thank you.

Important Message - From the Boys and Girls Club of Clifton:
Free Family Food Packs Distribution – Friday, June 19, 2020

Thanks to the generous donations from The Community FoodBank of New Jersey, the Boys & Girls Club of Clifton will distribute Family Food Packs on Friday, June 19th from Noon to 3:00 pm.

Enter the B&GCC parking lot via Orchard Street and pull up to the front of the BINGO Hall, as directed by staff.
Please remain in your vehicle and open your trunk.
Staff will place Family Packs into the vehicle.
Then exit via Colfax Avenue.

#whateverittakes #greatfuturesstarthere #cliftonnj

The June 4th Regular Meeting of the Board of Education
will be held virtually.

There will be no in-person session.
The meeting is scheduled to start at 7:00 PM.

The public is welcome to view a live stream via YouTube.
The link to this live stream will be posted to the district website, social media, and the online agenda located at
https://go.boarddocs.com/nj/clifton/Board.nsf/Public
approximately 5 minutes before the meeting begins.

If anyone wishes to contribute to the "public comment" section of the meeting, please email Mike Ucci, Board Secretary, at mucci@cliftonschools.net by 6:50 PM on the 4th. Please enter "Public Comment" in the subject line and be sure to include your name and address with your comments.

shared_text:
Clifton High School Mustang Band
May 25 at 10:28 AM ·

The Mustang Band remembers and honors America’s fallen heroes.

Without Clifton’s annual parade, we needed to find a way to keep the spirit of Memorial Day alive. For this virtual band performance, Mustang Band Members learned and recorded all new music at home. We even included some “found percussion” when traditional instruments were not available. Please enjoy a special arrangement of “You’re a Grand Old Flag.”

#TheShowbandoftheNortheast

Update (5/30): The Mustang Band would like to thank everyone for their support on our latest virtual band project. We're at nearly 10,000 views!

post_text:
A message from the Boys and Girls Club of Clifton:

Free Family Food Packs Distribution

Friday, May 15, 2020

Thanks to the generous donations from the New Jersey Community Foodbank, the Power of One and NJ Food and Clothing Rescue, the Boys & Girls Club of Clifton will distribute Family Food Packs on Friday, May 15th from Noon to 3:00 pm.

Enter the B&GCC parking lot via Orchard Street and pull up to the front of the BINGO Hall, as directed by staff.

Please remain in your vehicle and open your trunk.
Staff will place Family Packs into your vehicle. Then exit via Colfax Avenue.

Walk-Up Participants: Please bring reusable grocery bags and we will place food in bags.

Thank you

Thanks to donations from the New Jersey Community Food Bank and the Power of One. The Boys and Girls Club of Clifton will distribute over 500 family food packs on Friday, April 17 from 12:00 noon until approximately 2:00 PM.

Rice

Pasta O’s
Mac & cheese
Corn
Milk
Please be safe and healthy

post_text:
NJTV Learning Live: At-Home Learning Resources
https://www.njtvonline.org/

“At-home learning has begun and we want to be a resource for you. We’ll be providing more resources to support you and your network. Below you can find a curated list of free lessons, activities, and games from PBS KIDS and more to support remote learning and families at home.

NJTV, New Jersey’s public television network, in partnership with the NJEA and the New Jersey Department of Education, announced this week the launch of a new series of on-air instruction called NJTV Learning Live.

Weekdays starting this Monday, April 6th, kids can tune in to NJTV for on-air classes, taught by some of New Jersey’s finest public school teachers. On-air classes will be taught daily for grades three through six from 9 a.m. to 1 p.m. on NJTV.

WWMS shared an idea inspired by the children in Spain and Italy. An email to WWMS students stated, "Let's help spread the happiness! Simply create a rainbow and put it in your window with the rainbow facing the street. The rainbows can be made out of construction paper, paper with crayons/markers, washable paint, post its, etc. It is a simple way to spread hope and a feeling of connectedness in our community."

We can't wait to see the beautiful rainbows that you create! And you don't have to be a student to participate. Let's see how many rainbows we see around town. Feel free to reply to this post with a photo of your rainbow or post it on social media with the hashtags #itwillbeok. You can also include #cliftonstrong and #cliftonconnects.

post_text:
Dear Parents/Guardians, Faculty, Staff, and Community,

We are writing to inform you that the Clifton High School play, 9 to 5, The Musical, will be performed tonight at 7:00 pm without an audience. We will record the show, and we are attempting to procure the rights to broadcast the production on Clifton Cable. To that end, however, obtaining the rights may be a challenge due to stringent copyright issues. If possible, we will make every attempt to reschedule one show date later in the school year.

Please know that this difficult decision, made in consultation and with the recommendation of the Clifton Health Department, was the most viable solution to honor the hard work that our students and staff put into the production while keeping our community safe.

As always, we appreciate your patience and understanding as we make necessary modifications that best accommodate our students, staff, and community in the safest possible manner.

Thank you.

As new information emerges concerning COVID-19, Clifton Public Schools will close for students on Friday, March 13, 2020. Faculty and staff ONLY will report to school for a half-day of professional development on Friday, March 13, 2020, to prepare for distance learning.

All schools will be closed on Monday, March 16, 2020, for custodial staff to perform a deep cleaning of schools.

The district will determine if the situation warrants additional school closures before Tuesday, March 17, 2020, based on guidance from the NJ Department of Education as well as state and local health officials.

We will continue to update you as information becomes available. We appreciate your patience and understanding.

Edit: All after school activities are canceled on Monday, March 16.

On Monday, March 16th, all Clifton Public Schools will be closed for students to allow for our instructional staff to have collaborative time to plan for the possibility of school closures related to COVID-19. The modification to the school calendar will allow for our teachers and staff to prepare for extended online learning opportunities should we need to implement them.

In addition to other internal sanitization procedures that we have in place, the scheduled school closing will give our custodial staff time to complete thorough building cleanings.

We have heard from families and staff who are seeking information and understand that the community is concerned. We will continue to provide updates as we receive information.

We have been informed that "an 18-year-old from Clifton was exposed to coronavirus after having close contact on March 2 with a person in New York who was a known positive case. The Passaic County resident, who is not hospitalized, showed an onset of symptoms Friday."

𝗧𝗵𝗲 𝗖𝗹𝗶𝗳𝘁𝗼𝗻 𝗛𝗲𝗮𝗹𝘁𝗵 𝗗𝗲𝗽𝗮𝗿𝘁𝗺𝗲𝗻𝘁 𝗵𝗮𝘀 𝗻𝗼𝘁𝗶𝗳𝗶𝗲𝗱 𝘁𝗵𝗲 𝗱𝗶𝘀𝘁𝗿𝗶𝗰𝘁 𝘁𝗵𝗮𝘁 𝘁𝗵𝗲 𝗽𝗲𝗿𝘀𝗼𝗻 𝗶𝘀 𝗻𝗼𝘁 𝗮𝗳𝗳𝗶𝗹𝗶𝗮𝘁𝗲𝗱 𝘄𝗶𝘁𝗵 𝗖𝗹𝗶𝗳𝘁𝗼𝗻 𝗣𝘂𝗯𝗹𝗶𝗰 𝗦𝗰𝗵𝗼𝗼𝗹𝘀.

The district will continue to send updates as we receive them from the Clifton and NJ Department of Health.

Thank you.

Please be advised that there is a fake Instagram account "coronavirus_nj" claiming that there is a case of coronavirus in Clifton and suggesting that schools should close. This account is fake and has been reported.

Please be aware that any updated information or announcements will be issued by an official source.

We ask that you report any suspicious accounts to Instagram, Facebook, Twitter or any other social media platform to prevent the circulation of false information.

shared_text:
Clifton School 3
February 23 at 8:11 PM ·

AMAZING NEWS! Mrs. Park & Mr. Canova are jumping for joy for our Pennies for Patients fundraising results! This week, School 3 raised the following: Coins $119.63+Bills $623+Online $340=$1,082.63. Mrs. Park is so very proud to announce that we surpassed our school goal and thus far have raised a total of $6,018.68. Since we reached our school goal that means pies will be flying on Friday but which teachers will have the honor of throwing a pie? Continue to fundraise and on Friday, the teacher of the class who raise the 3rd & 2nd highest amount throws a pie at the counselor or secretary. The teacher of the class who raise the highest amount throws a pie at Mrs. Park our Principal. What a great cause with a fun twist so keep raising money. Teachers are rooting for their class to raise the most because they want to throw a pie!

Advisory:

Please be advised of a scam targeting PSE&G customers regarding meter replacement throughout the state, in Clifton, and surrounding areas. Please note that the scammers are “spoofing” numbers to resemble PSE&G on caller ID. Do not ever give money or personal information without confirming the true identity of the caller. The phone number for PSE&G is (800) 436-7734.

Please refer to the PSE&G news release for more information on protecting yourself from potential scam
activity. https://nj.pseg.com/newsroom/newsrelease64

Please share this information.
